cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a modification to neural network structures for better defending against adversarial attacks. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical and empirical analysis of the proposed method, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) categories.
